fields.title: Being Social..... thankfully its the Brain!
fields.article:
I grew up learning two faces of life. One through studying the life; the other one feeling the life. The more it unfolded, the higher my quest accrued. And in no time, my love for the subject of life, Biology raved up, the first face of life. Its not a static or incursive line of science. It opens up sequentially. It illuminates all worldly Kinships. A micrometer ( 1000th part of a small dot) cell encloses a nanometer ( let the microscope define it) DNA- the million codes which connect and calibrate the open-ended evolving life. How peculiar that can be?

Then comes the famous unsolved mysteries..why do blood carrying veins appear blue or the mechanism of goosebumps.. And then I, as a decently above average student, pondered whether thr cell divides or multiplies??? With just four taste buds how can we identify so many yumm delicacies.This one subject outnumbers all in the race of knowing science as a science.

Even after million years on going evolution, 90% of the human brain is still unlocked and how strong the heart is designed to pump blood up against the gravity.

I also evolved from this mind race and started teaching what I could master in 18years of educating myself. My love for this subject is more because it is bifacial... It may progress or retrogress. And then I sudden started empathizing my teacher since a teacher once used to be a student. Here I got acquainted with the second face of this subject. The complex softwares and sophisticated machineries inside a human body make it a prime social animal.

Does it sound weird? Let's come out of the subject love and talk more about this social animal being social. Adolescence is the age of oceans of feelings tiding up and down in flash of seconds. The diehard romantics became priceless relics in the sea of love and emotions with their knack of stringing the pearls of the love and sorrow. Sometimes its the strong desire or the rage on the fire..sometimes its the meaningless fear and sometimes the endless tears.

World says the heart Knows it all and does it all. Heart is emotional and it brings all kinds of aches to this social animal. The heart needs to stay happy for the human to live. Heart is such a sweetheart. But, the machine of softwares and the wirings, the BRAIN keeps the impulse go tic tac. Its such a bitter heart..no emotions no pain, no aches like heart breaks.

So, is it the heart which makes us a social being??? And the brain being anti- social!!!

Shockingly, it was never the heart who hears the cries who pushes for never ending tries.It only pumps the liquid just like any other motor pump do. It was always the Brain who stayed awake in your cries, turning he mental pain into physical stress. Heart always did just the job of pump. It never stopped when you didnt sleep, it never slowed when you stumbled. its just a pumping machine.

Forget about the heartaches, heart doesn't even know emotions and its thousands types. Its all the game of the hormones regulated by our very sensitive social organ and not the senseless pump. The heart is attacked by the dangerous levels of hormones, pressures and tensions caused in brain. We always cried from heart thinking heart soothes our failures.

Just imagine if you fail in any exam of life, no matter an exam or a love battle, your heart won't strengthen you. Brain eventually takes you out from the seemingly permanent impressions of the end. It pushes us to make the impossible possible by finding solutions to never ending problems and paves way of starting anew.

We start worrying when heart gives us pain but brain is just adept in covering up what it goes through in our difficult times. Gradually it gives up the emotions and that triggers the holocaust.

So next time when you are in a turmoil again, should you follow the heart or the brain??

Love your brain more than your heart for life is beautiful in the coalescence of the emotions developed by the brain. Give your ears to the silent whispers of its talks because it had been listening to you all your life. Let its talk now!

The Brain -- Our Social Organ.
